mportant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bo=
ttom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  pitching potential rescuers w=
ith a spreadsheet</a> showing that FTX was still solvent. That spreadsheet =
relied on billions of dollars of tokens =E2=80=94=C2=A0FTT but also weirder=
 things like Serum and Maps =E2=80=94=C2=A0that FTX had made up, that it ow=
ned most of, and that had no real independent market value. They were worth=
 billions as long as everyone believed in FTX, and nothing otherwise. By th=
e time Bankman-Fried was circulating the spreadsheet, they were worth nothi=
ng. But he only needed to find one person who believed.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusine=
ss.com/click/30059877.263533/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2=
